Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell(25.10)  swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell(25.10)

Name
       swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell  -  Identifies  the  regular buffer/in-
       verter and swaps it with always-on buffer/inverter

Syntax
       swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell

       [-help]

       [-cellMapFile <filename>]

       [-defaultAlwaysOnCell <AoCellNames>]

       [-nets <LPErrorNetList>]

       [-verbose]

       Identifies the regular buffer/inverter  and  swaps  it  with  always-on
       buffer/inverter.  The  regular  buffer/inverter  causes  the  LP error.
       Hence, this command fixes the LP error through the regular to always-on
       buffer/inverter swapping.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information  for each swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell parameter.
              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell

       -cellMapFile <filename>
              Specifies  the  map file name. The map file provides the equiva-
              lent driving strength between the regular buffer/inverter and AO
              buffer/inverter. This means that the timing will not be degraded
              with using this parameter, when the  mapped  always-on  cell  is
              swapped in.

              Following is the map file format:

              regularBufCellName AoBufCellName

       -defaultAlwaysOnCell <AoCellNames>
              Specifies  the  default  always-on buffer/inverter to be used to
              replace the regular buffer/inverter. When using default  always-
              on  buffer/inverter,  this parameter just corrects the LP error.
              Additionally, this parameter may degrade  the  timing,  and  you
              need to run optimization in flow.

       -nets <LPErrorNetList>
              Specifies  the  list of LP-error nets. By default, the swapRegu-
              larCellWithAlwaysOnCell command works on all the buffer/inverter
              trees. When this parameter is used, the  command  works  on  the
              buffer/inverter tree for the specified nets.

       -verbose
              Displays the detailed trace information for the specified nets.

Examples
              * The  following command swaps the incorrect regular buffer with
                AoBuf1, and the incorrect regular inverter with AoInverter1:

                swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell  -defaultAlwaysOnCell  "AoBuf1
                AoInverter1"

              * The  following  command swaps the incorrect regular buffer/in-
                verter using the specified mapping cells or  the  default  al-
                ways-on cells:

                swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell   -cellMapFile  mapfile1  -de-
                faultAlwaysOnCell "AoBuf1 AoInverter1"

              * The following command swaps the incorrect  regular  buffer/in-
                verter  using  the  default always-on cells for the buffer/in-
                verter trees along with the net1 and net2 paths:

                swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell -nets "net1 net2"  -defaultAl-
                waysOnCell "AoBuf1 AoInverter1"

              * The  following  command  swaps  the  incorrect buffer/inverter
                along with the net1 and net2 paths and displays  the  detailed
                trace information:

                swapRegularCellWithAlwaysOnCell  -nets "net1 net2" -defaultAl-
                waysOnCell "AoBuf1 AoInverter1 -verbose"

